<section id="searching-for-tasks" version="5.0" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
                                                xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
                                                xmlns:xl="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" >
  <title>Searching for tasks in ALM repositories</title>
  <anchor role="helpid" id="testSpecificationViewContextId">Test Case Browser</anchor>
  <anchor role="helpid" id="testExecViewContextId">Test Suite Browser</anchor>
  <para>
    On the fourth tab of the search dialog, you can search for tasks in any 
    repositories you have referenced in the Project.
  </para>
  <para>
    You can use this search if you have joined your Project to an external respository.
  </para>
  <para>
    Click ”<emphasis>Search</emphasis>” to start the search. 
    The results are shown in the Search Result View 
    (<xref linkend="using-the-search-result-view"/>).
  </para>
</section>